name: syncCurrentPlayItem
desc: Syncs the current player item with the server

name: onPlayerDestroyBlock
desc: Called when a player completes the destruction of a block

name: sendEnchantPacket
desc: GuiEnchantment uses this during multiplayer to tell PlayerControllerMP to send a packet indicating the enchantment action the player has taken.

name: getBlockReachDistance
desc: player reach distance = 4F

name: isInCreativeMode
desc: returns true if player is in creative mode

name: onPlayerDamageBlock
desc: Called when a player damages a block and updates damage counters

name: onPlayerRightClick
desc: Handles a players right click. Args: player, world, x, y, z, side, hitVec

name: sendSlotPacket
desc: Used in PlayerControllerMP to update the server with an ItemStack in a slot.

name: isNotCreative
desc: Checks if the player is not creative, used for checking if it should break a block instantly

name: attackEntity
desc: Attacks an entity

name: resetBlockRemoving
desc: Resets current block damage and field_78778_j

name: sendUseItem
desc: Notifies the server of things like consuming food, etc...

name: setTextureSize
desc: Returns the model renderer with the new texture parameters.

name: compileDisplayList
desc: Compiles a GL display list for this model

name: addBox
desc: Creates a textured box. Args: originX, originY, originZ, width, height, depth, scaleFactor.

name: addChild
desc: Sets the current box's rotation points and rotation angles to another box.

name: postRender
desc: Allows the changing of Angles after a box has been rendered

name: getNBTCompound
desc: Returns an NBTTagCompound with the server's name, IP and maybe acceptTextures.

name: getServerDataFromNBTCompound
desc: Takes an NBTTagCompound with 'name' and 'ip' keys, returns a ServerData instance.

name: addServerData
desc: Adds the given ServerData instance to the list.

name: getServerData
desc: Gets the ServerData instance stored for the given index in the list.

name: removeServerData
desc: Removes the ServerData instance stored for the given index in the list.

name: loadServerList
desc: Loads a list of servers from servers.dat, by running ServerData.getServerDataFromNBTCompound on each NBT compound found in the "servers" tag list.

name: setServer
desc: Sets the given index in the list to the given ServerData instance.

name: saveServerList
desc: Runs getNBTCompound on each ServerData instance, puts everything into a "servers" NBT list and writes it to servers.dat.

name: countServers
desc: Counts the number of ServerData instances in the list.

name: swapServers
desc: Takes two list indexes, and swaps their order around.

name: addBlockHitEffects
desc: Adds block hit particles for the specified block. Args: x, y, z, sideHit

name: renderParticles
desc: Renders all current particles. Args player, partialTickTime

name: getZSize
desc: Returns length of a bounding box

name: getYSize
desc: Returns height of a bounding box

name: getXSize
desc: Returns width of a bounding box

name: intersectsWith
desc: Returns whether the given bounding box intersects with this one. Args: structureboundingbox

name: intersectsWith
desc: Discover if a coordinate is inside the bounding box area.

name: offset
desc: Offsets the current bounding box by the specified coordinates. Args: x, y, z

name: getNewBoundingBox
desc: returns a new StructureBoundingBox with MAX values

name: expandTo
desc: Expands a bounding box's dimensions to include the supplied bounding box.

name: getComponentToAddBoundingBox
desc: used to project a possible new component Bounding Box - to check if it would cut anything already spawned

name: isVecInside
desc: Returns true if block is inside bounding box

name: callOcclusionQueryList
desc: Renders the occlusion query GL List

name: skipAllRenderPasses
desc: Checks if all render passes are to be skipped. Returns false if the renderer is not initialized

name: updateRenderer
desc: Will update this chunk renderer

name: getGLCallListForPass
desc: Takes in the pass the call list is being requested for. Args: renderPass

name: setDontDraw
desc: When called this renderer won't draw anymore until its gets initialized again

name: distanceToEntitySquared
desc: Returns the distance of this chunk renderer to the entity without performing the final normalizing square root, for performance reasons.

name: setPosition
desc: Sets a new position for the renderer and setting it up so it can be reloaded with the new data for that position

name: markDirty
desc: Marks the current renderer data as dirty and needing to be updated.

name: sortByDistanceToEntity
desc: Sorts the two world renderers according to their distance to a given entity.

name: isSnooperEnabled
desc: Returns whether snooping is enabled or not.

name: canCommandSenderUseCommand
desc: Returns true if the command sender is allowed to use the given command.

name: translateString
desc: Translates and formats the given string key with the given arguments.

name: getCommandSenderName
desc: Gets the name of this command sender (usually username, but possibly "Rcon")

name: resetLog
desc: Clears the RCon log

name: getLogContents
desc: Gets the contents of the RCon log

name: getDistance
desc: Gets the distance to the position. Args: x, y, z

name: setLocationAndAngles
desc: Sets the location and Yaw/Pitch of an entity in the world

name: getBrightness
desc: Gets how bright this entity is.

name: writeEntityToNBT
desc: (abstract) Protected helper method to write subclass entity data to NBT.

name: setFire
desc: Sets entity to burn for x amount of seconds, cannot lower amount of existing fire.

name: setBeenAttacked
desc: Sets that this entity has been attacked.

name: readFromNBT
desc: Reads the entity from NBT (calls an abstract helper method to read specialized data)

name: getParts
desc: Return the Entity parts making up this Entity (currently only for dragons)

name: getEntityString
desc: Returns the string that identifies this Entity's class

name: getEntityName
desc: Gets the username of the entity.

name: addVelocity
desc: Adds to the current velocity of the entity. Args: x, y, z

name: dropItem
desc: Drops an item stack at the entity's position. Args: itemID, count

name: isWet
desc: Checks if this entity is either in water or on an open air block in rain (used in wolves).

name: isBurning
desc: Returns true if the entity is on fire. Used by render to add the fire effect on rendering.

name: isEntityEqual
desc: Returns true if Entity argument is equal to this Entity

name: setWorld
desc: Sets the reference to the World object.

name: onEntityUpdate
desc: Gets called every tick from main Entity class

name: setSprinting
desc: Set sprinting switch for Entity.

name: getDistanceToEntity
desc: Returns the distance to the entity. Args: entity

name: getYOffset
desc: Returns the Y Offset of this entity.

name: getInventory
desc: returns the inventory of this entity (only used in EntityPlayerMP it seems)

name: playStepSound
desc: Plays step sound at given x, y, z for the entity

name: readEntityFromNBT
desc: (abstract) Protected helper method to read subclass entity data from NBT.

name: isOffsetPositionInLiquid
desc: Checks if the offset position from the entity's current position is inside of liquid. Args: x, y, z

name: addEntityID
desc: adds the ID of this entity to the NBT given

name: getLookVec
desc: returns a (normalized) vector of where this entity is looking

name: canTriggerWalking
desc: returns if this entity triggers Block.onEntityWalking on the blocks they walk on. used for spiders and wolves to prevent them from trampling crops

name: getMountedYOffset
desc: Returns the Y offset from the entity's position for any entity riding this one.

name: setOnFireFromLava
desc: Called whenever the entity is walking inside of lava.

name: getBoundingBox
desc: returns the bounding box for this entity

name: pushOutOfBlocks
desc: Adds velocity to push the entity out of blocks at the specified x, y, z position Args: x, y, z

name: newFloatNBTList
desc: Returns a new NBTTagList filled with the specified floats

name: isSprinting
desc: Get if the Entity is sprinting.

name: setFlag
desc: Enable or disable a entity flag, see getEntityFlag to read the know flags.

name: dropItemWithOffset
desc: Drops an item stack with a specified y offset. Args: itemID, count, yOffset

name: isInsideOfMaterial
desc: Checks if the current block the entity is within of the specified material type

name: handleLavaMovement
desc: Whether or not the current entity is in lava

name: moveFlying
desc: Used in both water and by flying objects

name: unmountEntity
desc: Called when a player unounts an entity.

name: setInPortal
desc: Called by portal blocks when an entity is within it.

name: updateFallState
desc: Takes in the distance the entity has fallen this tick and whether its on the ground to update the fall distance and deal fall damage if landing on the ground.  Args: distanceFallenThisTick, onGround

name: extinguish
desc: Removes fire from entity.

name: canBeCollidedWith
desc: Returns true if other Entities should be prevented from moving through this Entity.

name: getDistanceSqToEntity
desc: Returns the squared distance to the entity. Args: entity

name: fall
desc: Called when the mob is falling. Calculates and applies fall damage.

name: onUpdate
desc: Called to update the entity's position/logic.

name: handleWaterMovement
desc: Returns if this entity is in water and will end up adding the waters velocity to the entity

name: onKillEntity
desc: This method gets called when the entity kills another one.

name: canAttackWithItem
desc: If returns false, the item will not inflict any damage against entities.

name: kill
desc: sets the dead flag. Used when you fall off the bottom of the world.

name: onStruckByLightning
desc: Called when a lightning bolt hits the entity.

name: mountEntity
desc: Called when a player mounts an entity. e.g. mounts a pig, mounts a boat.

name: setPositionAndRotation
desc: Sets the entity's position and rotation. Args: posX, posY, posZ, yaw, pitch

name: dealFireDamage
desc: Will deal the specified amount of damage to the entity if the entity isn't immune to fire damage. Args: amountDamage

name: getFlag
desc: Returns true if the flag is active for the entity. Known flags: 0) is burning; 1) is sneaking; 2) is riding something; 3) is sprinting; 4) is eating

name: addToPlayerScore
desc: Adds a value to the player score. Currently not actually used and the entity passed in does nothing. Args: entity, scoreToAdd

name: interact
desc: Called when a player interacts with a mob. e.g. gets milk from a cow, gets into the saddle on a pig.

name: newDoubleNBTList
desc: creates a NBT list from the array of doubles passed to this function

name: isEntityAlive
desc: Checks whether target entity is alive.

name: isInWater
desc: Checks if this entity is inside water (if inWater field is true as a result of handleWaterMovement() returning true)

name: moveEntity
desc: Tries to moves the entity by the passed in displacement. Args: x, y, z

name: getDistanceSq
desc: Gets the squared distance to the position. Args: x, y, z

name: isSneaking
desc: Returns if this entity is sneaking.

name: isEntityInsideOpaqueBlock
desc: Checks if this entity is inside of an opaque block

name: setSneaking
desc: Sets the sneaking flag.

name: attackEntityFrom
desc: Called when the entity is attacked.

name: updateRidden
desc: Handles updating while being ridden by an entity

name: entityDropItem
desc: Drops an item at the position of the entity.

name: onCollideWithPlayer
desc: Called by a player entity when they collide with an entity

name: setRotation
desc: Sets the rotation of the entity. Args: yaw, pitch (both in degrees)

name: canBePushed
desc: Returns true if this entity should push and be pushed by other entities when colliding.

name: setSize
desc: Sets the width and height of the entity. Args: width, height

name: setDead
desc: Will get destroyed next tick.

name: setPosition
desc: Sets the x,y,z of the entity from the given parameters. Also seems to set up a bounding box.

name: applyEntityCollision
desc: Applies a velocity to each of the entities pushing them away from each other. Args: entity

name: writeToNBT
desc: Save the entity to NBT (calls an abstract helper method to write extra data)

name: setInWeb
desc: Sets the Entity inside a web block.

name: getCollisionBox
desc: Returns a boundingBox used to collide the entity with other entities and blocks. This enables the entity to be pushable on contact, like boats or minecarts.

name: onImpact
desc: Called when this EntityThrowable hits a block or entity.

name: getGravityVelocity
desc: Gets the amount of gravity to apply to the thrown entity with each tick.

name: setThrowableHeading
desc: Similar to setArrowHeading, it's point the throwable entity to a x, y, z direction.

name: getPotionDamage
desc: Returns the damage value of the thrown potion that this EntityPotion represents.

name: moveTowards
desc: The location the eye should float/move towards. Currently used for moving towards the nearest stronghold. Args: strongholdX, strongholdY, strongholdZ

name: onImpact
desc: Called when this EntityFireball hits a block or entity.

name: setKnockbackStrength
desc: Sets the amount of knockback the arrow applies when it hits a mob.

name: setArrowHeading
desc: Uses the provided coordinates as a heading and determines the velocity from it with the set force and random variance. Args: x, y, z, force, forceVariation

name: setTimeSinceHit
desc: Sets the time to count down from since the last time entity was hit.

name: setDamageTaken
desc: Sets the damage taken from the last hit.

name: getForwardDirection
desc: Gets the forward direction of the entity.

name: getTimeSinceHit
desc: Gets the time since the last hit.

name: setForwardDirection
desc: Sets the forward direction of the entity.

name: getDamageTaken
desc: Gets the damage taken from the last hit.

name: onInventoryChanged
desc: Called when an the contents of an Inventory change, usually

name: getInventoryStackLimit
desc: Returns the maximum stack size for a inventory slot. Seems to always be 64, possibly will be extended. *Isn't this more of a set than a get?*

name: decrStackSize
desc: Removes from an inventory slot (first arg) up to a specified number (second arg) of items and returns them in a new stack.

name: setInventorySlotContents
desc: Sets the given item stack to the specified slot in the inventory (can be crafting or armor sections).

name: isUseableByPlayer
desc: Do not make give this method the name canInteractWith because it clashes with Container

name: getStackInSlot
desc: Returns the stack in slot i

name: getSizeInventory
desc: Returns the number of slots in the inventory.

name: getInvName
desc: Returns the name of the inventory.

name: getStackInSlotOnClosing
desc: When some containers are closed they call this on each slot, then drop whatever it returns as an EntityItem - like when you close a workbench GUI.

name: addMapping
desc: Adds a new two-way mapping between the class and its string name in both hashmaps.

name: readFromNBT
desc: Reads a tile entity from NBT.

name: writeToNBT
desc: Writes a tile entity to NBT.

name: validate
desc: validates a tile entity

name: invalidate
desc: invalidates a tile entity

name: receiveClientEvent
desc: Called when a client event is received with the event number and argument, see World.sendClientEvent

name: updateEntity
desc: Allows the entity to update its state. Overridden in most subclasses, e.g. the mob spawner uses this to count ticks and creates a new spawn inside its implementation.

name: createAndLoadEntity
desc: Creates a new entity and loads its data from the specified NBT.

name: getDescriptionPacket
desc: Overriden in a sign to provide the text

name: isInvalid
desc: returns true if tile entity is invalid, false otherwise

name: updateContainingBlockInfo
desc: Causes the TileEntity to reset all it's cached values for it's container block, blockID, metaData and in the case of chests, the adjcacent chest check

name: getBlockMetadata
desc: Returns block data at the location of this entity (client-only).

name: getProgress
desc: Get interpolated progress value (between lastProgress and progress) given the fractional time between ticks as an argument.

name: getPistonOrientation
desc: Returns the orientation of the piston as an int

name: clearPistonTileEntity
desc: removes a pistons tile entity (and if the piston is moving, stops it)

name: isExtending
desc: Returns true if a piston is extending

name: getFilledSlots
desc: returns an integer with each bit specifying wether that slot of the stand contains a potion

name: getPotionResult
desc: Returns the new potion damage value after the specified item is applied as an ingredient to the specified potion.

name: anyPlayerInRange
desc: Returns true if there is a player in range (using World.getClosestPlayer)

name: updateDelay
desc: Sets the delay before a new spawn (base delay of 200 + random number up to 600).

name: getItemBurnTime
desc: Returns the number of ticks that the supplied fuel item will keep the furnace burning, or 0 if the item isn't fuel

name: smeltItem
desc: Turn one item from the furnace source stack into the appropriate smelted item in the furnace result stack

name: isBurning
desc: Returns true if the furnace is currently burning

name: isItemFuel
desc: Return true if item is a fuel source (getItemBurnTime() > 0).

name: canSmelt
desc: Returns true if the furnace can smelt an item, i.e. has a source item, destination stack isn't full, etc.

name: changePitch
desc: change pitch by -> (currentPitch + 1) % 25

name: triggerNote
desc: plays the stored note

name: checkForAdjacentChests
desc: Performs the check for adjacent chests to determine if this chest is double or not.

name: decrementAnimations
desc: Decrement the number of animations remaining. Only called on client side. This is used to handle the animation of receiving a block.

name: getTotalArmorValue
desc: Based on the damage values and maximum damage values of each armor item, returns the current armor value.

name: hasItemStack
desc: Returns true if the specified ItemStack exists in the inventory.

name: storeItemStack
desc: stores an itemstack in the users inventory

name: consumeInventoryItem
desc: removed one item of specified itemID from inventory (if it is in a stack, the stack size will reduce with 1)

name: dropAllItems
desc: Drop all armor and main inventory items.

name: getStrVsBlock
desc: Gets the strength of the current item (tool) against the specified block, 1.0f if not holding anything.

name: addItemStackToInventory
desc: Adds the item stack to the inventory, returns false if it is impossible.

name: writeToNBT
desc: Writes the inventory out as a list of compound tags. This is where the slot indices are used (+100 for armor, +80 for crafting).

name: readFromNBT
desc: Reads from the given tag list and fills the slots in the inventory with the correct items.

name: getDamageVsEntity
desc: Return damage vs an entity done by the current held weapon, or 1 if nothing is held

name: getInventorySlotContainItem
desc: Returns a slot index in main inventory containing a specific itemID

name: getFirstEmptyStack
desc: Returns the first item stack that is empty.

name: getCurrentItem
desc: Returns the item stack currently held by the player.

name: damageArmor
desc: Damages armor in each slot by the specified amount.

name: hasItem
desc: Get if a specifiied item id is inside the inventory.

name: storePartialItemStack
desc: This function stores as many items of an ItemStack as possible in a matching slot and returns the quantity of left over items.

name: canHarvestBlock
desc: Returns whether the current item (tool) can harvest from the specified block (actually get a result).

name: copyInventory
desc: Copy the ItemStack contents from another InventoryPlayer instance

name: getStackInRowAndColumn
desc: Returns the itemstack in the slot specified (Top left is 0, 0). Args: row, column

name: isMinecartPowered
desc: Is this minecart powered (Fuel > 0)

name: getDamage
desc: Gets the current amount of damage the minecart has taken. Decreases over time. The cart breaks when this is over 40.

name: setDamage
desc: Sets the current amount of damage the minecart has taken. Decreases over time. The cart breaks when this is over 40.

name: setMinecartPowered
desc: Set if this minecart is powered (Fuel > 0)

name: onValidSurface
desc: checks to make sure painting can be placed there

name: setDirection
desc: Sets the direction the painting faces.

name: getXpValue
desc: Returns the XP value of this XP orb.

name: getXPSplit
desc: Get a fragment of the maximum experience points value for the supplied value of experience points value.

name: getSoundVolume
desc: Returns the volume for the sounds this mob makes.

name: getCanSpawnHere
desc: Checks if the entity's current position is a valid location to spawn this entity.

name: isPlayerSleeping
desc: Returns whether player is sleeping or not

name: onDeathUpdate
desc: handles entity death timer, experience orb and particle creation

name: isMovementBlocked
desc: Dead and sleeping entities cannot move

name: isWithinHomeDistanceCurrentPosition
desc: Returns true if entity is within home distance from current position

name: moveEntityWithHeading
desc: Moves the entity based on the specified heading.  Args: strafe, forward

name: isClientWorld
desc: Returns whether the entity is in a local (client) world

name: eatGrassBonus
desc: This function applies the benefits of growing back wool and faster growing up to the acting entity. (This function is used in the AIEatGrass)

name: getSpeedModifier
desc: This method returns a value to be applied directly to entity speed, this factor is less than 1 when a slowdown potion effect is applied, more than 1 when a haste potion effect is applied and 2 for fleeing entities.

name: isOnLadder
desc: returns true if this entity is by a ladder, false otherwise

name: getHurtSound
desc: Returns the sound this mob makes when it is hurt.

name: despawnEntity
desc: Makes the entity despawn if requirements are reached

name: setAttackTarget
desc: Sets the active target the Task system uses for tracking

name: faceEntity
desc: Changes pitch and yaw so that the entity calling the function is facing the entity provided as an argument.

name: getTalkInterval
desc: Get number of ticks, at least during which the living entity will be silent.

name: dropFewItems
desc: Drop 0-2 items of this living's type

name: updateAITick
desc: main AI tick function, replaces updateEntityActionState

name: isChild
desc: If Animal, checks if the age timer is negative

name: getDropItemId
desc: Returns the item ID for the item the mob drops on death.

name: setPositionAndUpdate
desc: Sets the position of the entity and updates the 'last' variables

name: getEntitySenses
desc: returns the EntitySenses Object for the EntityLiving

name: onLivingUpdate
desc: Called frequently so the entity can update its state every tick as required. For example, zombies and skeletons use this to react to sunlight and start to burn.

name: getAttackTarget
desc: Gets the active target the Task system uses for tracking

name: getLivingSound
desc: Returns the sound this mob makes while it's alive.

name: getMaxSpawnedInChunk
desc: Will return how many at most can spawn in a chunk at once.

name: playLivingSound
desc: Plays living's sound at its position

name: onDeath
desc: Called when the mob's health reaches 0.

name: getVerticalFaceSpeed
desc: The speed it takes to move the entityliving's rotationPitch through the faceEntity method. This is only currently use in wolves.

name: getSoundPitch
desc: Gets the pitch of living sounds in living entities.

name: isAIEnabled
desc: Returns true if the newer Entity AI code should be run

name: knockBack
desc: knocks back this entity

name: applyArmorCalculations
desc: Reduces damage, depending on armor

name: spawnExplosionParticle
desc: Spawns an explosion particle around the Entity's location

name: getTotalArmorValue
desc: Returns the current armor value as determined by a call to InventoryPlayer.getTotalArmorValue

name: setAIMoveSpeed
desc: set the movespeed used for the new AI system

name: getActivePotionEffect
desc: returns the PotionEffect for the supplied Potion if it is active, null otherwise.

name: isEntityUndead
desc: Returns true if this entity is undead.

name: updateRotation
desc: Arguments: current rotation, intended rotation, max increment.

name: jump
desc: Causes this entity to do an upwards motion (jumping).

name: damageEntity
desc: Deals damage to the entity. If its a EntityPlayer then will take damage from the armor first and then health second with the reduced value. Args: damageAmount

name: getCreatureAttribute
desc: Get this Entity's EnumCreatureAttribute

name: renderBrokenItemStack
desc: Renders broken item particles using the given ItemStack

name: applyPotionDamageCalculations
desc: Reduces damage, depending on potions

name: getDeathSound
desc: Returns the sound this mob makes on death.

name: getLook
desc: interpolated look vector

name: decreaseAirSupply
desc: Decrements the entity's air supply when underwater

name: isPlayer
desc: Only use is to identify if class is an instance of player for experience dropping

name: canEntityBeSeen
desc: returns true if the entity provided in the argument can be seen. (Raytrace)

name: getAIMoveSpeed
desc: the movespeed used for the new AI system

name: addPotionEffect
desc: adds a PotionEffect to the entity

name: heal
desc: Heal living entity (param: amount of half-hearts)

name: canDespawn
desc: Determines if an entity can be despawned, used on idle far away entities

name: getExperiencePoints
desc: Get the experience points the entity currently has.

name: getEntityToAttack
desc: returns the target Entity

name: setPathToEntity
desc: sets the pathToEntity

name: updateWanderPath
desc: Time remaining during which the Animal is sped up and flees.

name: isMovementCeased
desc: Disables a mob's ability to move on its own while true.

name: hasPath
desc: if the entity got a PathEntity it returns true, else false

name: findPlayerToAttack
desc: Finds the closest player within 16 blocks to attack, or null if this Entity isn't interested in attacking (Animals, Spiders at day, peaceful PigZombies).

name: getBlockPathWeight
desc: Takes a coordinate in and returns a weight to determine how likely this creature will try to path to the block. Args: x, y, z

name: setTarget
desc: Sets the entity which is to be attacked.

name: attackEntity
desc: Basic mob attack. Default to touch of death in EntityCreature. Overridden by each mob to define their attack.

name: isCourseTraversable
desc: True if the ghast has an unobstructed line of travel to the waypoint.

name: canDamagePlayer
desc: Indicates weather the slime is able to damage the player (based upon the slime's size)

name: getSlimeParticle
desc: Returns the name of a particle effect that may be randomly created by EntitySlime.onUpdate()

name: getJumpSound
desc: Returns the name of the sound played when the slime jumps.

name: makesSoundOnLand
desc: Returns true if the slime makes a sound when it lands after a jump (based upon the slime's size)

name: getAttackStrength
desc: Gets the amount of damage dealt to the player when "attacked" by the slime.

name: getJumpDelay
desc: Gets the amount of time the slime needs to wait between jumps.

name: makesSoundOnJump
desc: Returns true if the slime makes a sound when it jumps (based upon the slime's size)

name: getSlimeSize
desc: Returns the size of the slime.

name: isValidLightLevel
desc: Checks to make sure the light is not too bright where the mob is spawning

name: teleportToEntity
desc: Teleport the enderman to another entity

name: setCarryingData
desc: Set the metadata of the block an enderman carries

name: setCarried
desc: Set the id of the block an enderman carries

name: teleportRandomly
desc: Teleport the enderman to a random nearby position

name: shouldAttackPlayer
desc: Checks to see if this enderman should be attacking this player

name: getCarried
desc: Get the id of the block an enderman carries

name: getCarryingData
desc: Get the metadata of the block an enderman carries

name: teleportTo
desc: Teleport the enderman

name: setCreeperState
desc: Sets the state of creeper, -1 to idle and 1 to be 'in fuse'

name: getPowered
desc: Returns true if the creeper is powered by a lightning bolt.

name: getCreeperState
desc: Returns the current state of creeper, -1 is idle, 1 is 'in fuse'

name: becomeAngryAt
desc: Causes this PigZombie to become angry at the supplied Entity (which will be a player).

name: setBesideClimbableBlock
desc: Updates the WatchableObject (Byte) created in entityInit(), setting it to 0x01 if par1 is true or 0x00 if it is false.

name: isBesideClimbableBlock
desc: Returns true if the WatchableObject (Byte) is 0x01 otherwise returns false. The WatchableObject is updated using setBesideClimableBlock.

name: setGrowingAge
desc: The age value may be negative or positive or zero. If it's negative, it get's incremented on each tick, if it's positive, it get's decremented each tick. With a negative value the Entity is considered a child.

name: getGrowingAge
desc: The age value may be negative or positive or zero. If it's negative, it get's incremented on each tick, if it's positive, it get's decremented each tick. Don't confuse this with EntityLiving.getAge. With a negative value the Entity is considered a child.

name: procreate
desc: Creates a baby animal according to the animal type of the target at the actual position and spawns 'love' particles.

name: isWheat
desc: Checks if the parameter is an wheat item.

name: canMateWith
desc: Returns true if the mob is currently able to mate with the specified mob.

name: spawnBabyAnimal
desc: This function is used when two same-species animals in 'love mode' breed to generate the new baby animal.

name: isInLove
desc: Returns if the entity is currently in 'love mode'.

name: getSheared
desc: returns true if a sheeps wool has been sheared

name: setSheared
desc: make a sheep sheared if set to true

name: getRandomFleeceColor
desc: This method is called when a sheep spawns in the world to select the color of sheep fleece.

name: setSaddled
desc: Set or remove the saddle of the pig.

name: getSaddled
desc: Returns true if the pig is saddled.

name: playTameEffect
desc: Play the taming effect, will either be hearts or smoke depending on status

name: setAngry
desc: Sets whether this wolf is angry or not.

name: isAngry
desc: Determines whether this wolf is angry or not.

name: superAttackFrom
desc: Returns a super of attackEntityFrom in EntityDragonBase, because the normal attackEntityFrom is overriden

name: setNewTarget
desc: Sets a new target for the flight AI. It can be a random coordinate or a nearby player.

name: updateDragonEnderCrystal
desc: Updates the state of the enderdragon's current endercrystal.

name: collideWithEntities
desc: Pushes all entities inside the list away from the enderdragon.

name: attackEntitiesInList
desc: Attacks all entities inside this list, dealing 5 hearts of damage.

name: destroyBlocksInAABB
desc: Destroys all blocks that aren't associated with 'The End' inside the given bounding box.

name: simplifyAngle
desc: Simplifies the value of a number by adding/subtracting 180 to the point that the number is between -180 and 180.

name: getMovementOffsets
desc: Returns a double[3] array with movement offsets, used to calculate trailing tail/neck positions. [0] = yaw offset, [1] = y offset, [2] = unused, always 0. Parameters: buffer index offset, partial ticks.

name: createEnderPortal
desc: Creates the ender portal leading back to the normal world after defeating the enderdragon.

name: shouldHeal
desc: Checks if the player's health is not full and not zero.

name: getSpawnChunk
desc: Returns the coordinates to respawn the player based on last bed that the player sleep.

name: wakeUpPlayer
desc: Wake up the player if they're sleeping.

name: addMovementStat
desc: Adds a value to a movement statistic field - like run, walk, swin or climb.

name: onItemPickup
desc: Called whenever an item is picked up from walking over it. Args: pickedUpEntity, stackSize

name: isPVPEnabled
desc: returns if pvp is enabled or not

name: getInventoryEnderChest
desc: Returns the InventoryEnderChest of this player.

name: displayGUIDispenser
desc: Displays the dipsenser GUI for the passed in dispenser entity. Args: TileEntityDispenser

name: displayGUIChest
desc: Displays the GUI for interacting with a chest inventory. Args: chestInventory

name: setItemInUse
desc: sets the itemInUse when the use item button is clicked. Args: itemstack, int maxItemUseDuration

name: onCriticalHit
desc: Called when the player performs a critical hit on the Entity. Args: entity that was hit critically

name: updateItemUse
desc: Plays sounds and makes particles for item in use state

name: joinEntityItemWithWorld
desc: Joins the passed in entity item with the world. Args: entityItem

name: displayGUIEditSign
desc: Displays the GUI for editing a sign. Args: tileEntitySign

name: addMountedMovementStat
desc: Adds a value to a mounted movement statistic field - by minecart, boat, or pig.

name: sendPlayerAbilities
desc: Sends the player's abilities to the server (if there is one).

name: displayGUIBrewingStand
desc: Displays the GUI for interacting with a brewing stand.

name: sleepInBedAt
desc: puts player to sleep on specified bed if possible

name: dropPlayerItemWithRandomChoice
desc: Args: itemstack, flag

name: addExhaustion
desc: increases exhaustion level by supplied amount

name: dropPlayerItem
desc: Args: itemstack - called when player drops an item stack that's not in his inventory (like items still placed in a workbench while the workbench'es GUI gets closed)

name: alertWolves
desc: Called when the player attack or gets attacked, it's alert all wolves in the area that are owned by the player to join the attack or defend the player.

name: addExperience
desc: Add experience points to player.

name: getFoodStats
desc: Returns the player's FoodStats object.

name: isPlayerFullyAsleep
desc: Returns whether or not the player is asleep and the screen has fully faded.

name: destroyCurrentEquippedItem
desc: Destroys the currently equipped item from the player's inventory.

name: triggerAchievement
desc: Will trigger the specified trigger.

name: removeExperience
desc: Removes the specified number of experience levels.

name: setGameType
desc: Sets the player's game type

name: addChatMessage
desc: Add a chat message to the player

name: onItemUseFinish
desc: Used for when item use count runs out, ie: eating completed

name: swingItem
desc: Swings the item the player is holding.

name: isUsingItem
desc: Checks if the entity is currently using an item (e.g., bow, food, sword) by holding down the useItemButton

name: dropOneItem
desc: Called when player presses the drop item key

name: displayGUIFurnace
desc: Displays the furnace GUI for the passed in furnace entity. Args: tileEntityFurnace

name: getCurrentEquippedItem
desc: Returns the currently being used item by the player.

name: getSwingSpeedModifier
desc: Returns the swing speed modifier

name: displayGUIBook
desc: Displays the GUI for interacting with a book.

name: clonePlayer
desc: Copies the values from the given player into this player if boolean par2 is true. Always clones Ender Chest Inventory.

name: xpBarCap
desc: This method returns the cap amount of experience that the experience bar can hold. With each level, the experience cap on the player's experience bar is raised by 10.

name: closeScreen
desc: set current crafting inventory back to the 2x2 square

name: increaseLevel
desc: This method increases the player's experience level by one.

name: getCurrentPlayerStrVsBlock
desc: Returns how strong the player is against the specified block at this moment

name: verifyRespawnCoordinates
desc: Ensure that a block enabling respawning exists at the specified coordinates and find an empty space nearby to spawn.

name: displayWorkbenchGUI
desc: Displays the crafting GUI for a workbench.

name: attackTargetEntityWithCurrentItem
desc: Attacks for the player the targeted entity with the currently equipped item.  The equipped item has hitEntity called on it. Args: targetEntity

name: resetHeight
desc: sets the players height back to normal after doing things like sleeping and dieing

name: canHarvestBlock
desc: Checks if the player has the ability to harvest a block (checks current inventory item for a tool if necessary)

name: setSpawnChunk
desc: Defines a spawn coordinate to player spawn. Used by bed after the player sleep on it.

name: addStat
desc: Adds a value to a statistic field.

name: isInBed
desc: Checks if the player is currently in a bed

name: updateCraftingInventory
desc: update the crafting window inventory with the items in the list

name: updateCraftingInventorySlot
desc: inform the player of a change in a single slot

name: updateCraftingInventoryInfo
desc: send information about the crafting inventory to the client(currently only for furnace times)

name: updateHeldItem
desc: updates item held by mouse, This method always returns before doing anything...

name: getNextWindowId
desc: get the next window id to use

name: getTileEntityInfo
desc: gets description packets from all TileEntity's that override func_20070

name: handleFalling
desc: process player falling based on movement packet

name: getEquipmentInSlot
desc: 0: Tool in Hand; 1-4: Armor

name: closeCraftingGui
desc: close the current crafting gui

name: startServer
desc: Initialises the server and starts it.

name: logSevere
desc: Log severe error message

name: getFile
desc: Returns a File object from the specified string.

name: getPlayerNamesAsList
desc: Returns a list of usernames of all connected players

name: getServerOwner
desc: Returns the username of the server owner (for integrated servers)

name: getServerPort
desc: Gets serverPort.

name: outputPercentRemaining
desc: used to display a percent remaining given text and the percentage

name: getWorldManager
desc: gets the worldServer by the given dimension

name: setServerOwner
desc: Sets the username of the owner of this server (in the case of an integrated server)

name: playersOnline
desc: Returns the number of players on the server

name: getPort
desc: Returns the server port

name: logWarning
desc: logs the warning same as: logger.warning(String);

name: isDebuggingEnabled
desc: Returns true if debugging is enabled, false otherwise

name: clearCurrentTask
desc: set current task to null and set its percentage to 0

name: log
desc: Logs the message with a level of INFO.

name: getVersion
desc: Returns the server version string

name: getKeyPair
desc: Gets KeyPair instanced in MinecraftServer.

name: handleRConCommand
desc: Handle a command received by an RCon instance

name: stopServer
desc: Saves all necessary data as preparation for stopping the server.

name: initiateShutdown
desc: Sets the serverRunning variable to false, in order to get the server to shut down.

name: getMotd
desc: Returns the server message of the day

name: getMaxPlayers
desc: Returns the maximum number of players allowed on the server

name: getServer
desc: Gets mcServer.

name: getHostname
desc: Returns the server hostname

name: saveProperties
desc: Saves all of the server properties to the properties file

name: getIntProperty
desc: Returns the specified property value as an int, or a default if the property doesn't exist

name: setProperty
desc: Saves an Object with the given property name

name: getSettingsFilename
desc: Returns the filename where server properties are stored

name: getStringProperty
desc: Returns the specified property value as a String, or a default if the property doesn't exist

name: getCauseStackTraceOrString
desc: Gets the stack trace of the Throwable that caused this crash report, or if that fails, the cause .toString().

name: addCrashSectionThrowable
desc: Adds a Crashreport section with the given name with the given Throwable

name: addCrashSectionCallable
desc: Adds a Crashreport section with the given name with the value set to the result of the given Callable;

name: getDescription
desc: Returns the description of the Crash Report.

name: getCompleteReport
desc: Gets the complete report with headers, stack trace, and different sections as a string.

name: getWittyComment
desc: Gets a random witty comment for inclusion in this CrashReport

name: getSectionsInStringBuilder
desc: Gets the various sections of the crash report into the given StringBuilder

name: addCrashSection
desc: Adds a Crashreport section with the given name with the given value (convered .toString())

name: saveToFile
desc: Saves the complete crash report to the given File.

name: addTabCompletionOptions
desc: Adds the strings available in this command to the given list of tab completion options.

name: canCommandSenderUseCommand
desc: Returns true if the given command sender is allowed to use this command.

name: joinString
desc: Joins the given string array, starting with the given index, into a space seperated string.

name: getCommandSenderAsPlayer
desc: Returns the given ICommandSender as a EntityPlayer or throw an exception.

name: doesStringStartWith
desc: Returns true if the given substring is exactly equal to the start of the given string (case insensitive).

name: compareNameTo
desc: Compares the name of this command to the name of the given command.

name: parseInt
desc: Parses an int from the given string.

name: joinNiceString
desc: Joins the given string array into a "x, y, and z" seperated string.

name: parseIntWithMin
desc: Parses an int from the given sring with a specified minimum.

name: setAdminCommander
desc: Sets the static IAdminCommander.

name: getListOfStringsMatchingLastWord
desc: Returns a List of strings (chosen from the given strings) which the last word in the given string array is a beginning-match for. (Tab completion).

name: getListOfStringsFromIterableMatchingLastWord
desc: Returns a List of strings (chosen from the given string iterable) which the last word in the given string array is a beginning-match for. (Tab completion).

name: parseIntBounded
desc: Parses an int from the given string within a specified bound.

name: getGameModeFromCommand
desc: Gets the Game Mode specified in the command.

name: getWittyComment
desc: Returns a random "witty" comment.

name: addTime
desc: Adds (or removes) time in the server object.

name: notifyAdmins
desc: Sends a message to the admins of the server from a given CommandSender with the given resource string and given extra srings. If the int par2 is even or zero, the original sender is also notified.

name: getAllowedCharacters
desc: Load the font.txt resource file, that is on UTF-8 format. This file contains the characters that minecraft can render Strings on screen.

name: getDistanceSquared
desc: Returns the squared distance between this coordinates and the coordinates given as argument.

name: compareChunkCoordinate
desc: Compare the coordinate with another coordinate

name: addPlayer
desc: adds this connection to the list of currently connected players

name: handleNetworkListenThread
desc: Handles all incoming connections and packets

name: onBlockHarvested
desc: Called when the block is attempted to be harvested

name: updateTick
desc: Ticks the block if it's been scheduled

name: setHardness
desc: Sets how many hits it takes to break a block.

name: setCreativeTab
desc: sets the CreativeTab to display this block on

name: canPlaceBlockOnSide
desc: checks to see if you can place this block can be placed on that side of a block: BlockLever overrides

name: getBlockTextureFromSide
desc: Returns the block texture based on the side being looked at.  Args: side

name: canProvidePower
desc: Can this block provide power. Only wire currently seems to have this change based on its state.

name: canBlockStay
desc: Can this block stay at this position.  Similar to canPlaceBlockAt except gets checked often with plants.

name: isIndirectlyPoweringTo
desc: Is this block indirectly powering the block on the specified side

name: getRenderType
desc: The type of render function that is called for this block

name: getBlockTextureFromSideAndMetadata
desc: From the specified side and block metadata retrieves the blocks texture. Args: side, metadata

name: tickRate
desc: How many world ticks before ticking

name: onBlockPlacedBy
desc: Called when the block is placed in the world.

name: onBlockAdded
desc: Called whenever the block is added into the world. Args: world, x, y, z

name: onNeighborBlockChange
desc: Lets the block know when one of its neighbor changes. Doesn't know which neighbor changed (coordinates passed are their own) Args: x, y, z, neighbor blockID

name: setBlockName
desc: set name of block from language file

name: isPoweringTo
desc: Is this block powering the block on the specified side

name: onFallenUpon
desc: Block's chance to react to an entity falling on it.

name: onBlockDestroyedByExplosion
desc: Called upon the block being destroyed by an explosion

name: setLightOpacity
desc: Sets how much light is blocked going through this block. Returns the object for convenience in constructing.

name: onEntityCollidedWithBlock
desc: Triggered whenever an entity collides with this block (enters into the block). Args: world, x, y, z, entity

name: addCollidingBlockToList
desc: if the specified block is in the given AABB, add its collision bounding box to the given list

name: getCollisionBoundingBoxFromPool
desc: Returns a bounding box from the pool of bounding boxes (this means this box can change after the pool has been cleared to be reused)

name: setBlockUnbreakable
desc: This method will make the hardness of the block equals to -1, and the block is indestructible.

name: getEnableStats
desc: Return the state of blocks statistics flags - if the block is counted for mined and placed.

name: collisionRayTrace
desc: Ray traces through the blocks collision from start vector to end vector returning a ray trace hit. Args: world, x, y, z, startVec, endVec

name: createStackedBlock
desc: Returns an item stack containing a single instance of the current block type. 'i' is the block's subtype/damage and is ignored for blocks which do not support subtypes. Blocks which cannot be harvested should return null.

name: getTickRandomly
desc: Returns whether or not this block is of a type that needs random ticking. Called for ref-counting purposes by ExtendedBlockStorage in order to broadly cull a chunk from the random chunk update list for efficiency's sake.

name: onBlockEventReceived
desc: Called when the block receives a BlockEvent - see World.addBlockEvent. By default, passes it on to the tile entity at this location. Args: world, x, y, z, blockID, EventID, event parameter

name: setStepSound
desc: Sets the footstep sound for the block. Returns the object for convenience in constructing.

name: idDropped
desc: Returns the ID of the items to drop on destruction.

name: renderAsNormalBlock
desc: If this block doesn't render as an ordinary block it will return False (examples: signs, buttons, stairs, etc)

name: isVecInsideXYBounds
desc: Checks if a vector is within the X and Y bounds of the block.

name: onEntityWalking
desc: Called whenever an entity is walking on top of this block. Args: world, x, y, z, entity

name: harvestBlock
desc: Called when the player destroys a block with an item that can harvest it. (i, j, k) are the coordinates of the block and l is the block's subtype/damage.

name: setResistance
desc: Sets the the blocks resistance to explosions. Returns the object for convenience in constructing.

name: disableStats
desc: Disable statistics for the block, the block will no count for mined or placed.

name: dropBlockAsItem
desc: Drops the specified block items

name: onBlockDestroyedByPlayer
desc: Called right before the block is destroyed by a player.  Args: world, x, y, z, metaData

name: damageDropped
desc: Determines the damage on the item the block drops. Used in cloth and wood.

name: setLightValue
desc: Sets the amount of light emitted by a block from 0.0f to 1.0f (converts internally to 0-15). Returns the object for convenience in constructing.

name: velocityToAddToEntity
desc: Can add to the passed in vector for a movement vector to be applied to the entity. Args: x, y, z, entity, vec3d

name: setBlockBoundsBasedOnState
desc: Updates the blocks bounds based on its current state. Args: world, x, y, z

name: onBlockActivated
desc: Called upon block activation (right click on the block.)

name: getExplosionResistance
desc: Returns how much this block can resist explosions from the passed in entity.

name: setBlockBounds
desc: Sets the bounds of the block.  minX, minY, minZ, maxX, maxY, maxZ

name: canSilkHarvest
desc: Return true if a player with Silk Touch can harvest this block directly, and not its normal drops.

name: setTickRandomly
desc: Sets whether this block type will receive random update ticks

name: getPlayerRelativeBlockHardness
desc: Gets the hardness of block at the given coordinates in the given world, relative to the ability of the given EntityPlayer.

name: quantityDroppedWithBonus
desc: Returns the usual quantity dropped by the block plus a bonus of 1 to 'i' (inclusive).

name: setRequiresSelfNotify
desc: Blocks with this attribute will not notify all near blocks when it's metadata change. The default behavior is always notify every neightbor block when anything changes.

name: canCollideCheck
desc: Returns whether this block is collideable based on the arguments passed in Args: blockMetaData, unknownFlag

name: dropBlockAsItemWithChance
desc: Drops the block items with a specified chance of dropping the specified items

name: getMobilityFlag
desc: Returns the mobility information of the block, 0 = free, 1 = can't push but can move over, 2 = total immobility and stop pistons

name: isVecInsideYZBounds
desc: Checks if a vector is within the Y and Z bounds of the block.

name: setBlockBoundsForItemRender
desc: Sets the block's bounds for rendering it as an item

name: onBlockClicked
desc: Called when the block is clicked by a player. Args: x, y, z, entityPlayer

name: isBlockSolid
desc: Returns Returns true if the given side of this block type should be rendered (if it's solid or not), if the adjacent block is at the given coordinates. Args: blockAccess, x, y, z, side

name: quantityDropped
desc: Returns the quantity of items to drop on block destruction.

name: isOpaqueCube
desc: Is this block (a) opaque and (b) a full 1m cube?  This determines whether or not to render the shared face of two adjacent blocks and also whether the player can attach torches, redstone wire, etc to this block.

name: onSetBlockIDWithMetaData
desc: Called when this block is set (with meta data).

name: initializeBlock
desc: This method is called on a block after all other blocks gets already created. You can use it to reference and configure something on the block that needs the others ones.

name: dropBlockAsItem_do
desc: Spawns EntityItem in the world for the given ItemStack if the world is not remote.

name: canPlaceBlockAt
desc: Checks to see if its valid to put this block at the specified coordinates. Args: world, x, y, z

name: translateBlockName
desc: gets the localized version of the name of this block using StatCollector.translateToLocal. Used for the statistic page.

name: getBlockHardness
desc: Returns the block hardness at a location. Args: world, x, y, z

name: isCollidable
desc: Returns if this block is collidable (only used by Fire). Args: x, y, z

name: isVecInsideXZBounds
desc: Checks if a vector is within the X and Z bounds of the block.

name: onTimeChanged
desc: Called when the time changes.

name: updatePistonState
desc: handles attempts to extend or retract the piston.

name: canPushBlock
desc: returns true if the piston can push the specified block

name: canExtend
desc: checks to see if this piston could push the blocks in front of it.

name: isIndirectlyPowered
desc: checks the block to that side to see if it is indirectly powered.

name: isExtended
desc: Determine if the metadata is related to something powered.

name: tryExtend
desc: attempts to extend the piston. returns false if impossible.

name: determineOrientation
desc: gets the way this piston should face for that entity that placed it.

name: getOrientation
desc: returns an int which describes the direction the piston faces

name: canSnowStay
desc: Checks if this snow block can stay at this location.

name: canPlaceTorchOn
desc: Gets if we can place a torch on a block.

name: dropTorchIfCantStay
desc: Tests if the block can remain at its current location and will drop as an item if it is unable to stay. Returns True if it can stay and False if it drops. Args: world, x, y, z

name: isIndirectlyPowered
desc: Returns true or false based on whether the block the torch is attached to is providing indirect power.

name: isValidSupportBlock
desc: Checks if the block ID is a valid support block for the trap door to connect with. If it is not the trapdoor is dropped into the world.

name: canVineStay
desc: Returns if the vine can stay in the world. It also changes the metadata according to neighboring blocks.

name: canBePlacedOn
desc: returns true if a vine can be placed on that block (checks for render as normal block and if it is solid)

name: getMetadataForBlockType
desc: Returns the metadata to use when a Silverfish hides in the block. Sets the block to BlockSilverfish with this metadata. It changes the displayed texture client side to look like a normal block.

name: getPosingIdByMetadata
desc: Gets the blockID of the block this block is pretending to be according to this block's metadata.

name: canThisPaneConnectToThisBlockID
desc: Gets passed in the blockID of the block adjacent and supposed to return true if its allowed to connect to the type of blockID passed in. Args: blockID

name: isEnderEyeInserted
desc: checks if an ender eye has been inserted into the frame block. parameters: metadata

name: checkBlockCoordValid
desc: Checks if current block pos is valid, if not, breaks the block as dropable item. Used for reed and cactus.

name: updateAndPropagateCurrentStrength
desc: Sets the strength of the wire current (0-15) for this block based on neighboring blocks and propagates to neighboring redstone wires

name: isPoweredOrRepeater
desc: Returns true if the block coordinate passed can provide power, or is a redstone wire, or if its a repeater that is powered.

name: getMaxCurrentStrength
desc: Returns the current strength at the specified block if it is greater than the passed value, or the passed value otherwise. Signature: (world, x, y, z, strength)

name: notifyWireNeighborsOfNeighborChange
desc: Calls World.notifyBlocksOfNeighborChange() for all neighboring blocks, but only if the given block is a redstone wire.

name: isPowerProviderOrWire
desc: Returns true if the block coordinate passed can provide power, or is a redstone wire.

name: glow
desc: The redstone ore glows.

name: sparkle
desc: The redstone ore sparkles.

name: isPoweredBlockRail
desc: Return true if the blocks passed is a power related rail.

name: isRailBlockAt
desc: Returns true if the block at the coordinates of world passed is a valid rail block (current is rail, powered or detector).

name: refreshTrackShape
desc: Completely recalculates the track shape based on neighboring tracks

name: isNeighborRailPowered
desc: Powered minecart rail is conductive like wire, so check for powered neighbors

name: isPowered
desc: Returns true if the block is power related rail.

name: isRailBlock
desc: Return true if the parameter is a blockID for a valid rail block (current is rail, powered or detector).

name: isRailPassingPower
desc: Returns true if the specified rail is passing power to its neighbor

name: setStateIfMinecartInteractsWithRail
desc: Update the detector rail power state if a minecart enter, stays or leave the block.

name: tryToFall
desc: If there is space to fall below will start this block falling

name: canFallBelow
desc: Checks to see if the sand can fall into the block below it

name: setStateIfMobInteractsWithPlate
desc: Checks if there are mobs on the plate. If a mob is on the plate and it is off, it turns it on, and vice versa.

name: checkIfAttachedToBlock
desc: Checks if the block is attached to another block. If it is not, it returns false and drops the block as an item. If it is it returns true.

name: getFlowDecay
desc: Returns the amount of fluid decay at the coordinates, or -1 if the block at the coordinates is not the same material as the fluid.

name: getFluidHeightPercent
desc: Returns the percentage of the fluid block that is air, based on the given flow decay of the fluid.

name: checkForHarden
desc: Forces lava to check to see if it is colliding with water, and then decide what it should harden to.

name: triggerLavaMixEffects
desc: Creates fizzing sound and smoke. Used when lava flows over block or mixes with water.

name: getFlowVector
desc: Returns a vector indicating the direction and intensity of fluid flow.

name: getEffectiveFlowDecay
desc: Returns the flow decay but converts values indicating falling liquid (values >=8) to their effective source block value of zero.

name: updateFlow
desc: Updates the flow for the BlockFlowing object.

name: getOptimalFlowDirections
desc: Returns a boolean array indicating which flow directions are optimal based on each direction's calculated flow cost. Each array index corresponds to one of the four cardinal directions. A value of true indicates the direction is optimal.

name: liquidCanDisplaceBlock
desc: Returns true if the block at the coordinates can be displaced by the liquid.

name: blockBlocksFlow
desc: Returns true if block at coords blocks fluids

name: calculateFlowCost
desc: calculateFlowCost(World world, int x, int y, int z, int accumulatedCost, int previousDirectionOfFlow) - Used to determine the path of least resistance, this method returns the lowest possible flow cost for the direction of flow indicated. Each necessary horizontal flow adds to the flow cost.

name: flowIntoBlock
desc: flowIntoBlock(World world, int x, int y, int z, int newFlowDecay) - Flows into the block at the coordinates and changes the block type to the liquid.

name: getSmallestFlowDecay
desc: getSmallestFlowDecay(World world, intx, int y, int z, int currentSmallestFlowDecay) - Looks up the flow decay at the coordinates given and returns the smaller of this value or the provided currentSmallestFlowDecay. If one value is valid and the other isn't, the valid value will be returned. Valid values are >= 0. Flow decay is the amount that a liquid has dissipated. 0 indicates a source block.

name: setNotStationary
desc: Changes the block ID to that of an updating fluid.

name: isFlammable
desc: Checks to see if the block is flammable.

name: getDirection
desc: Returns the orentation value from the specified metadata

name: isFenceGateOpen
desc: Returns if the fence gate is open according to its metadata.

name: isBedOccupied
desc: Return whether or not the bed is occupied.

name: getNearestEmptyChunkCoordinates
desc: Gets the nearest empty chunk coordinates for the player to wake up from a bed into.

name: setBounds
